result.formatted_address: 61 Caine Rd., Mid-Levels, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Elephant Grounds Mid-Levels

reviews.text:
Visited the restaurant as a part of a trip to Hong Kong.
The place is really good for breakfast and the coffee is great, they also have cold brew coffee which was very special and refreshing.
The is a medium variety of things to eat, most of them include eggs in one way or another, we ate eggs Benedict and liked it a lot.
But the thing we liked the most was the attitude of the employees, so nice and welcoming.
Always nice coffee and great service. It would be great if you could have a more air conditioned indoor and outdoor area though. Thanks!
Reasonably priced, good portions, quality food. Wonderful iced Americano.
nice place you can take a rest and drink a cup of coffee in the top of the mid levels

My "home" on the way! Love the short menu full of quality and taste. Sharp service, nit place, great location (!) and such a western upper/hip class clientele. Coffee always comes excellent. Extra tip😎:perfect place for weekend brunch. Just take the escalators then to go around Soho. Do expect though that weekends are quity busy before 13.00.
